'Cheese.'

02:34.905 --> 02:37.533
- 'Three, two, one, go!'
- 'Cheese.'

02:37.658 --> 02:39.126
'Matty Burton!'

02:54.508 --> 02:55.475
Hey, you.

02:56.593 --> 02:57.765
Hey, you, Mimi.

02:58.470 --> 03:00.438
Yo. Yo, Mimi.

03:00.555 --> 03:02.774
How you doing? How you doing?

03:02.891 --> 03:05.064
Eh? All right, beautiful?

03:05.185 --> 03:06.732
Yeah. Where's Mama?

03:06.853 --> 03:08.605
Where's Mama, eh?

03:09.648 --> 03:12.652
It's all sticky. Yeah, it's all sticky.

03:12.776 --> 03:13.948
Yeah!

03:14.069 --> 03:15.992
Daddy have some of your toast?

03:16.113 --> 03:18.457
Have some of Mimi's toast? Daddy eat it?

03:18.573 --> 03:20.075
No? Daddy gonna eat it.

03:21.159 --> 03:23.753
Eh? Daddy can't eat any of your toast.
I got boobies.

03:23.870 --> 03:25.463
I've got to get rid of my boobies.

03:25.580 --> 03:28.254
- I've got bigger boobies than Mummy.
- Oh, is that right?

03:28.959 --> 03:31.929
If Daddy keeps that talk up,
there'll be no booby off Mummy for a month.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.467
- Oi, come here.
- What?

03:33.588 --> 03:36.888
Come here.

03:37.008 --> 03:38.476
Get here.

03:40.053 --> 03:41.145
Thank you.

03:42.472 --> 03:44.270
- I love you.
- Good.

03:49.229 --> 03:51.903
After this fight, I'll take you out
somewhere nice to eat.

03:52.023 --> 03:53.900
Sounds good.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.619
Anywhere you wanna go. It's your choice.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.114
We can go to Nando's.

03:59.614 --> 04:01.241
- Berni Inn.
- Wow!

04:01.366 --> 04:03.585
- Harvester.
- You spoil me.

04:04.411 --> 04:06.209
You deserve it, kid.

04:15.881 --> 04:18.305
Matthew! Mia's right there. It's a bit weird.

04:18.425 --> 04:19.517
Oh?

04:19.634 --> 04:20.851
Mimi?

04:20.969 --> 04:22.391
Come here, baby.

04:22.512 --> 04:24.606
There you go, look. Let's turn you around.

04:25.515 --> 04:28.644
- EMMA: This is so wrong!
- MATTY: Don't look at Mummy and Daddy.

04:28.769 --> 04:31.614
MATTY: You watch the birdies, look.
There you go.

04:34.483 --> 04:37.032
JOURNALIST:
Matty, you lost your father recently.

04:37.152 --> 04:39.701
He was with you in the corner
for your first 33 fights.

04:40.739 --> 04:43.288
What difference will it make
when you walk to the ring?

04:43.408 --> 04:44.830
Will his thoughts be in your head?

04:44.951 --> 04:48.455
Yeah, definitely.
I'll fight in honour of my father.

04:48.580 --> 04:51.459
You know what?
No disrespect to his pops an' all that,

04:51.583 --> 04:55.053
but it wouldn't matter
if he was here or not, he'd still lose.

04:55.170 --> 04:57.298
Every single person
who goes against me goes down,

04:57.422 --> 04:58.890
regardless of who's in his corner.

04:59.007 --> 05:01.180
JOURNALIST:
You should show Matty more respect.

05:01.301 --> 05:02.723
Respect for what? What's he done?

05:02.844 --> 05:05.893
His father was part of boxing folklore.
Surely that's wrong.

05:06.014 --> 05:08.267
All right, go on.
What do you wanna say about your dad?

05:09.810 --> 05:12.359
It's, er... It's fine.

05:12.896 --> 05:14.899
I'm just so grateful
that before he passed away,

05:15.023 --> 05:19.529
I was able to bring the title home
and also I've got a beautiful daughter.

05:19.653 --> 05:22.873
I'm just glad that he was able
to hold her before he left us.

05:22.989 --> 05:25.208
JOURNALIST:
Has that given you extra motivation?

05:25.325 --> 05:27.623
It's another person in my life to protect.

05:27.744 --> 05:29.872
It's just that extra bit of fire.

05:29.996 --> 05:32.420
Having that bit of extra motivation
is gonna help me.

05:32.541 --> 05:34.134
This is his most important fight.

05:34.251 --> 05:37.380
It's the most important fight
of my life, apparently.

05:38.088 --> 05:40.762
Matty, you're fighting Andre The Future.

05:40.882 --> 05:45.058
This is billed as "The Future Is Here".
Do you feel like you've been written off?

05:45.178 --> 05:49.274
If it's all about the future,
the past is gonna bite him on his arse.

05:49.391 --> 05:50.768
(LAUGHTER)

05:50.892 --> 05:54.067
This guy's losing all the time,
and he won this on a default.

05:54.187 --> 05:56.360
It's my duty to go out there and defend it.

05:56.481 --> 05:57.858
He's never been better.

05:57.983 --> 06:00.486
He knows he didn't earn it.
He is not the true champion.

06:00.610 --> 06:03.364
I might not be the best technical boxer,
but I'm the world champion.

06:03.488 --> 06:07.163
A true champion defeats his opponents.
They don't pull out because of an injury.

06:07.284 --> 06:08.911
He's not a true champion.

06:09.035 --> 06:11.288
It will be interesting to see
who's around him

06:11.413 --> 06:12.756
after he loses on the 22nd.

06:13.790 --> 06:15.667
I'm gonna knock him out, take that belt home.

06:15.792 --> 06:18.341
We're gonna dance on his grave
and celebrate his life.

06:18.461 --> 06:19.462
AUDIENCE: Ooh!

06:19.588 --> 06:21.181
MAN: Go on, Matt. Go on!

06:21.298 --> 06:24.973
WARREN: Shall we wrap that up?
Thank you very much for coming down.

06:25.093 --> 06:27.972
- We'll see you fight night.
- Come on, Granddad!

06:28.096 --> 06:32.693
ANDRE: This belt is mine.
Last time you're gonna feel that belt.

06:32.809 --> 06:35.153
Hey, look at me.
What are you looking at them for?

06:35.270 --> 06:36.738
Look at me. You ashamed to look at me?

06:38.440 --> 06:41.615
You want me to look you in the eye?
I'll look you in the eye. There you go.

06:41.735 --> 06:43.453
I'm gonna take your head off.

06:45.947 --> 06:47.745
This is a life-changer for you.

06:48.283 --> 06:50.411
Understand that. It's a life-changer.

07:12.849 --> 07:13.816
Hey!

07:14.726 --> 07:16.569
You're not asleep, are you?

07:16.686 --> 07:18.233
Eh? You're wakies.

07:18.355 --> 07:19.982
You're wakies, eh?

07:20.106 --> 07:21.949
Ah, my baby.

07:22.734 --> 07:24.737
My baby girl, eh?

07:26.196 --> 07:27.789
What's Daddy gonna do?

07:28.531 --> 07:30.408
What's Daddy gonna do, Mimi?

07:30.533 --> 07:31.955
Eh?

07:32.077 --> 07:34.796
Eh? Shall I whup his arse?

07:34.913 --> 07:37.792
Eh? Shall I smoke his boots?

07:37.916 --> 07:41.796
Shall I? Shall I take him
into the deep water and drown him?

07:41.920 --> 07:42.967
Yeah?

07:43.713 --> 07:44.885
Eh?

07:47.384 --> 07:48.511
I love you.

07:49.803 --> 07:51.350
Phwoar.

07:51.471 --> 07:54.441
You've tinkered, haven't you?
You've tinkered, haven't you?

07:54.557 --> 07:56.730
Yeah, you smelly bum-bum.

07:57.936 --> 07:59.654
Come on, let's change your bum.

07:59.771 --> 08:00.772
Yeah.

08:00.897 --> 08:02.695
Slow-mo. There, there, there.

08:03.191 --> 08:04.192
- Feel it?
- Yeah.

08:05.652 --> 08:07.370
There's the shot. Relax on it.

08:08.738 --> 08:09.739
There he is.

08:09.864 --> 08:11.582
Sit down on those hooks.

08:11.700 --> 08:12.701
Again.

08:13.243 --> 08:15.211
There he is. There he is.

08:15.328 --> 08:16.671
Spring back in with that right.

08:28.425 --> 08:29.267
Time.

08:36.890 --> 08:38.234
Here.

08:38.351 --> 08:39.193
Nice.

08:39.309 --> 08:40.732
Another one in.

08:43.063 --> 08:44.441
Exhale. Nice and slow.

08:44.566 --> 08:45.818
Slow it down. That's it.

08:46.401 --> 08:47.823
RICHIE: Come on.

08:47.944 --> 08:49.287
Been eating Mimi's treats?

08:50.864 --> 08:52.241
It'll come off in the bath.

08:53.700 --> 08:54.827
Let's go. Eight.

08:56.995 --> 08:58.042
Sharp stuff.

08:58.163 --> 09:00.791
Three, four, five, relax.

09:12.927 --> 09:17.729
And now to the scales, the WBO
middleweight champion of the world,

09:17.849 --> 09:20.568
Matty Burton.

09:20.685 --> 09:23.234
(CHEERING)

09:23.354 --> 09:27.700
- MATTY BURTON: 11 stone, 4 pounds.
- CROWD: Matty! Matty! Matty!

09:27.817 --> 09:29.990
Yes! Come on!

09:30.111 --> 09:32.079
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

09:42.916 --> 09:44.634
STEVE BUNCE: 'Andre, your best chance

09:44.751 --> 09:47.129
'is because he's, according
to you, over the hill.'

09:47.253 --> 09:49.881
ANDRE: 'The best of him is gone,
but I could beat the best of him.

09:50.006 --> 09:52.225
'What is the best of him? Please tell me.

09:52.342 --> 09:54.686
'The best of him ain't touching
the lowest of me.'

09:54.803 --> 09:58.933
'From my point of view, Steve,
look, this fight is about experience,

09:59.057 --> 10:01.060
'and he's never gone in deep in his career.'

10:01.184 --> 10:03.903
'You're going down.
It's a life-changer for you.

10:04.020 --> 10:07.240
'I ain't lost a single fight, right?
I've had 18 fights, 16 knockouts.

10:07.357 --> 10:09.906
'He's a sluggish fighter.
Just stands there, takes beats.

10:10.026 --> 10:13.280
'What's there to fear or respect?
People are gonna go, "Matty who?"'

10:23.206 --> 10:25.425
JACKIE: Here he is. You all right, champ?

10:25.542 --> 10:27.215
- Yeah, mate.
- JACKIE: Give us your bag.

10:27.335 --> 10:29.338
- Thanks.
- I'll get it in the car for you.

10:30.588 --> 10:31.589
Come here.

10:33.299 --> 10:35.222
Don't worry, we'll look after him.

10:35.343 --> 10:37.141
- See you, Jackie.
- All right, ta-ra.

10:37.720 --> 10:39.347
- Take your time, bro.
- Thanks, mate.

10:48.606 --> 10:50.199
Emma.

10:51.901 --> 10:53.244
Look at me.

10:57.866 --> 11:00.915
When I come back through that door
in a few hours' time,

11:01.035 --> 11:03.288
I'm still gonna be champion of the world.

11:06.416 --> 11:07.588
Number one.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.797
I've just gotta do this. It's what I do.

11:13.715 --> 11:14.716
Yeah.

11:17.677 --> 11:18.678
I'd better go.

11:21.639 --> 11:24.267
Can you knock him out quick?

11:24.392 --> 11:26.611
- I wish it was that easy.
- (LAUGHS)

11:31.232 --> 11:32.279
I love you.

11:33.234 --> 11:34.281
Good.

11:51.002 --> 11:52.925
RICHIE: Spread your fingers. Okay?

11:56.758 --> 11:59.261
- RICHIE: Thanks, gents.
- MAN: Good luck.

11:59.385 --> 12:00.887
RICHIE: Thank you.

12:29.332 --> 12:32.086
(# THUMPING MUSIC)

12:36.965 --> 12:41.352
And now, ladies and gentlemen,
entering the arena, the champion,

12:41.469 --> 12:46.316
the one and only Matty Burton!

12:46.432 --> 12:48.605
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

12:52.021 --> 12:53.773
WOMAN: Punch his lights out!

12:54.357 --> 12:55.734
WOMAN: Come on, Matty!

12:58.528 --> 12:59.620
Okay, bring him out.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.835
We love you, Matty!

13:17.088 --> 13:19.056
Yeah, you can't run away now.

13:21.926 --> 13:23.769
Come on, Granddad. What do you say?

13:29.642 --> 13:30.769
(CHEERING)

13:33.396 --> 13:38.823
And now, ladies and gentlemen,
it's Big Fight time.

13:38.943 --> 13:42.368
This is a contest of 12 three-minute rounds

13:42.488 --> 13:47.494
to decide the WBO middleweight
championship of the world.

13:47.618 --> 13:48.915
In you come.

13:49.871 --> 13:52.124
I gave you instructions in the dressing room.

13:52.248 --> 13:53.215
Life-changer.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.336
I say "break", you break. Touch 'em up.

13:55.460 --> 13:57.588
- You ain't tasted pain.
- Best of luck, gents.

13:57.712 --> 14:00.466
He's got no class. Here you are.
Hard work's done, mate.

14:00.590 --> 14:03.014
Homework's done. Do what you do best.

14:03.134 --> 14:04.761
CROWD: Matty! Matty! Matty!

14:06.179 --> 14:08.022
Get on that jab. Don't chase him.

14:14.437 --> 14:15.564
